Francisco's queer communities into the identity-based groups we see today. In its vivid re-creation of bar and drag life, its absorbing portrait of central figures in the communities, and its provocative chronicling of this period in the country's most transgressive city, Wide-Open Town offers a fascinating and lively new chapter of American queer history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aGaysxHistoryxCaliforniaxSan FranciscoxCaliforniaxSan Francisco. 0aGayszCaliforniazSan FranciscoxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh  a20th century.  aamerica.  aamerican history.  abar scene.  acalifornia.  acivil rights activists.  acivil rights.  acourt records.  agay and lesbian.  agay culture.  ahistorians.  ahomophiles.  ahomosexuality.  aideological.  algbtq.  anonfiction.  aoral histories.  apolitical activism.  aqueer bars.  aqueer communities.  aqueer history.  aqueer studies.  aregional history.  asan francisco.  asocial identity.  asocial justice.  asocial science.  atourist districts.  atransgender community.  atransgressive.  aturn of the century.  aunited states.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093874840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520938748423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520938748/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles